Description:
The role involves being part of a very dynamic laundry team and be the brand custodian for Rin.
Key Responsibilities
:
·
Building a holistic understanding of consumers and shoppers of Rin;
·
Responsible for driving both topline and bottom line brand growth and achieving brand share & communication targets;
·
Managing brand’s P&L; and ensuring a profitable contribution to portfolio;
·
Leading and delivering innovation, renovation & NILG projects as per agreed milestones/timelines and to the high quality standards set;
·
Development of activity based 12-month brand marketing planning and execution including TV, Activation, PR, mobile, print, social media and outdoor in line with global category strategy and brand vision plan;
·
Spearheading cross functional teams to deliver business objectives from inception to execution;
·
Monitoring and analysis of sales volumes, market share, media and perception trends, and competitor activity;
·
Work with media and creative agencies to brief, design and deliver specific elements of projects and marketing campaigns;
·
Be part of demand forecast and reporting team and ensuring S&OP; delivery;
·
Analyze and report brand’s progress based on syndicated research (Retail Audit & Consumer Panel etc.), brand health indicators and internal sales database.
Core Skills Required
:
·
Project Management – ability to lead and manage multiple projects across category, working with cross-functional team to ensure on time in full deliver;
·
Analytical Power – critical thinking skills, ability to evaluate financial performance, projects P&L; and understanding consumers to highlight gaps;
·
Ability to adapt and multi-task in a fast-paced/high-change environment;
·
Proficient in MS Project, Power point & Excel;
·
Confident with new IT tools.
Competencies:
·
Project Leadership and strong follow up;
·
Strong Communication and persuasive skills;
·
Bias for Action and informed as well as quick decision making;
·
Ability to think out of the box and take calculated risks;
·
Growth Mindset along with accountability.
Education:
Bachelors degree in relevant discipline.
Experience:
Ideally 2-3 years of relevant marketing/brand experience.
